Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of Germanic origin (via French  <b>Adélaïde</b> ), from <i>adal</i> ‘noble’ + <i>heid</i> ‘kind, sort’. It was borne in the 10th century by the wife of the Holy Roman Emperor Otto the Great. She became regent after his death and was revered as a saint. The given name increased in popularity in England during the 19th century, when it was borne by the wife of King William IV; she was the daughter of the ruler of the German duchy of Saxe-Meiningen. The Australian city of Adelaide was named in her honour."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Adélaïde DE BEZIERS was born in 1105, in Narbonne, Aude, France, her father, Guillaume Arnaud de Béziers, was 27 and her mother, Metheline Trencavel, was 33. She married Raymond Vicomte de Béziers, Comte d'Agbe, d'Albi, de Carcassonne et Rasez about 1125. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. She died in 1164, in Carcassonne, Aude, France, at the age of 59."},"et":{"1105–1164":"1105–1164","1090–1136":"1090–1136","1125–Female":"1125–Surnud","1098–1167":"1098–1167","1132–1188":"1132–1188","1140–Female":"1140–Surnud","1078–1105":"1078–1105","1072–1152":"1072–1152","1090":"1090","ABT 1125":"umbes 1125","1132":"1132","1164":"1164","1098":"1098","1152":"1152","1140":"1140","1072":"1072","1105":"1105","1125":"1125","1136":"1136","1167":"1167","1078":"1078","1188":"1188","about 1132":"umbes 1132","Narbonne, Aude, Languedoc-Roussillon, France":"Narbonne, Aude, Languedoc-Roussillon, Prantsusmaa","Béziers, Hérault, Occitanie, France":"Béziers, Hérault, Occitanie, Prantsusmaa","Carcassonne, 11000, Aude, France":"Carcassonne, Aude, Prantsusmaa","Narbonne, 11100, Aude, France":"Narbonne, Aude, Prantsusmaa","France":"Prantsusmaa","Béziers,  Hérault, Occitanie, France":"Béziers, Hérault, Occitanie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1105–1164":"1105–1164","1090–1136":"1090–1136","1125–Female":"1125–Kuollut","1098–1167":"1098–1167","1132–1188":"1132–1188","1140–Female":"1140–Kuollu